{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "01 Public Collection Lifecycle",
  "description": "Flow scenario for a complete public collection lifecycle in Postman Local View.",
  "flow": {
    "description": "Scenario steps:\n1. Register a temporary owner user.\n2. Log in and capture the session token.\n3. Create a PUBLIC collection.\n4. List collections anonymously and verify the new collection appears.\n5. Fetch the collection anonymously.\n6. Update the collection metadata.\n7. Verify the updated collection publicly.\n8. Delete the collection for cleanup.\n\nRecommended collection requests: Auth/01-03 and Collections/01-04,16.",
